n class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2526846\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Okt 07, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent wide\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104djv1665702697642.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/djv1665702697642.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/djv1665702697642.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"djv1665702697642\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                 \n Uniface Installation Directory Structure\n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"djv1665702697642__uniface_installation_directory_structure_197159\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">The Uniface product directory contains the <span class=\"ph filepath\">common</span> and\n         <span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface</span> main subdirectories.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djv1665702697642__p_d65552e1_d65553e1_d65554e1\">The Uniface main subdirectories include the following\n         content:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"djv1665702697642__li_d28490e1_d28491e1_d28492e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">common</span>—includes common components, executable and binary files, configuration files, and a single Tomcat web server.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"djv1665702697642__li_d28493e1_d28494e1_d28495e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">uniface</span>—contain all files that are specific to the individual product, including components, utilities and configuration files.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djv1665702697642__p_d65555e1_d65556e1_d65557e1\">The <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common</span> and <span class=\"ph filepath\">/uniface</span> directories contain a number of subdirectories, such as:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"djv1665702697642__li_d28496e1_d28497e1_d28498e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">adm</span>—initialization and assignment files that set the environment context for each application.\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"djv1665702697642__li_d28499e1_d28500e1_d28501e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">components</span>—application components\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"djv1665702697642__li_d28502e1_d28503e1_d28504e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">sql</span>—SQL scripts for creating Repository tables in supported databases\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"djv1665702697642__li_d28505e1_d28506e1_d28507e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">usys</span>—UAR files containing the runtime components required for deployment\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"djv1665702697642__li_d28508e1_d28509e1_d28510e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">webapps</span>—virtual root directory for the product's web applications. The Tomcat web server (located in <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common</span>) is configured to use these directory locations.\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djv1665702697642__p_d65558e1_d65559e1_d65560e1\">On Windows, the default location of the data directory is\n               <span class=\"ph filepath\">C:\\Users\\<var class=\"keyword varname\">UserAccount</var>\\Documents\\<span class=\"keyword\">Rocket® Uniface</span>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">Edition</var></span>. It contains the data outputs created with the\n         Uniface IDE and servers, including the Repository, compiled components, log files, and\n         other files required by your application. </p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"djv1665702697642__p_d65564e1_d65565e1_d65566e1\">A number of these directories are specified in predefined USYS path logicals, ensuring that each Uniface product or application can locate the files appropriate to its environment.</p>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526846\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2526846\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Uniface Installation Directory Structure Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Okt 07, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Uniface Installation Directory Structure The Uniface product directory contains the common and uniface main subdirectories. The Uniface main subdirectories include the following content: common —includes common components, executable and binary files, configuration files, and a single Tomcat web server. uniface —contain all files that are specific to the individual product, including components, utilities and configuration files. The /common and /uniface directories contain a number of subdirectories, such as: adm —initialization and assignment files that set the environment context for each application. components —application components sql —SQL scripts for creating Repository tables in supported databases usys —UAR files containing the runtime components required for deployment webapps —virtual root directory for the product's web applications. The Tomcat web server (located in /common ) is configured to use these directory locations. On Windows, the default location of the data directory is C:\\Users\\ UserAccount \\Documents\\ Rocket® Uniface Edition . It contains the data outputs created with the Uniface IDE and servers, including the Repository, compiled components, log files, and other files required by your application. A number of these directories are specified in predefined USYS path logicals, ensuring that each Uniface product or application can locate the files appropriate to its environment. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}